# Next.js 16

This is NOT standard Next.js — APIs and conventions may differ from older versions.

Before writing or changing Next.js code, read the relevant guide in `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`. Heed deprecation notices.

## App Router

- Routes live in `app/` (`page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, etc.)
- Server Components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed (state, effects, events)
- Global styles: `app/globals.css` imports `app/theme.css`
- Metadata exported from `layout.tsx` or `page.tsx`

## Patterns

```tsx
// ✅ Server Component (default)
export default function Page() {
  return <main>...</main>;
}

// ✅ Client Component — only when interactive
"use client";
export function Counter() { ... }
```

## Do not

- Put UI components in `app/` unless route-specific
- Re-add create-next-app boilerplate
- Use Pages Router (`pages/`) patterns
